Title(3, "Alignment");
Format("For RISC-V processors, the addresses of data in memory should be aligned when ^Tload^t/^Tstore^t instructions act. An exception will arise if it does not match the alignment.\nx86 series have no the limit, but the times of accessing needed will be increasing if no alignment.\n");

